Commit Message: Initial commit: put latest revision of v115 under version control

Minor changes to the Makefile and sn3d.c to make the revision at
compiletime known to the code. From now on binary filenames end
on .exe (update your jobfiles).

Readme file has now some basic information on howto checkout a working
    copy from the server

Added another section to the Makefile to define compilers and flags
for the new Juelich BlueGene/Q system "juqueen".

After some experiments with the compiler flags on JUQUEEN I found out
that interprocedural analysis does not work. Since this is standard at
optimization levels -O4 and -O5 it needs to be turned off. As the best
compromise between runtime and stability I found

 -O4 -qarch=qp -qtune=qp -qnoipa -qinline -qthreaded -qsmp

This is now the new standard setting for JUQUEEN in the Makefile.

This version introduces a new global array "energy_deposition" to
record how much radioactive energy was deposited by gammas and
positrons in each modelgrid cell. This information is written to the
estimator files as an additional number (last entry of a row,
preceding entries are unchanged).

This is "artis_118" from Stromlo.
This is the version with most of the changes for doing NLTE level populations/NT ionization implemented but NOT tested.
The hope is that this will eventually let us do nebular spectra. But DO NOT USE IT as it is.

Nebular code version as of 3 Jul - end of Stockholm visit. This DOESN'T WORK. Important change is (i) debuging of alpha_sp's and (ii) introduction of a partition function/stat weight ratio for the ionization approximation in NLTE.

new input format and data structures for multilevel photoionization

first version of the code to handle photoionisation to multiple target
states. So far this affects the calculated recombination rates.

grid cell dependent functions have not been updated yet.

parameterise phixs table resolution

photoionization cross sections were previously hard coded to be defined
for factors of 1.0,1.1,1.2,1.3,etc of nu_edge. The spacing is now
parameterised by NPHIXSNUFACTOR with a default value of 0.1.
further changes to parameterise phixs table resolution

further work to support multilevel photoionisation

Now produces a decent spectrum!
Also some improvements to code formatting and changes to prevent
compiler warnings.

Code cleanup and missing photoioniz. probability

Fix indentation, remove type casting of calloc/malloc, and added
missing phis_probability factor to sigma_cf in rpkt

update macroatom and rpkt with ionization transitions

also code cleanup and fixes for parameterised phixs increment and table
size.

2022 November release (#29)

- For kilonovae, enable seeding with initial energy in the q column of
model.txt
- Add kilonova test calculation to GitHub actions (to test alpha/beta
decays and thermalisation)
- exspec: read all packets files into memory if total size is below a
limit (maxpktmem_mb = 6000). This makes angle-resolved files much faster
to generate.
- Prepend each log line with the date and time
- Fix escaping direction bin for non-normalised direction vectors
- Reduce memory fragmentation by making block allocation for atomic
transition arrays and sharing on node
- Use C++ std library search functions (faster and less code)

A 1D Sim+2010 Sub-MCh test with classic options gives about an 8-11%
decrease in run time.

Add BFCOOLING_USELEVELPOPNOTIONPOP option (#31)

This option is off by default for all configurations.

Fix classic test MD5 sums (#35)

Non-exact output match could be due to GitHub Actions running on a
different CPU type or a compiler version change.

Read 2 phixs files for hybrid atomic data simulations (#34)

Added functionality to make it possible to use both phixsdata.txt and phixsdata_v2.txt files in the same simulation as they are in different formats. The phixsdata.txt file is used in the atomic data sets that we have typically used for classic-mode simulations (e.g. the cd23 or big_gf-4 atomic data sets described by Kromer & Sim, 2009) while the phixsdata_v2.txt is used in the more detailed atomic data set described by Shingles et al. (2020) which is based off the atomic data compilation of CMFGEN with some modifications. This functionality makes it possible to run simulations with hybrid atomic data sets where the atomic data set each ion is sourced from can be chosen.

v2023.5 (#30)

### Physically significant changes:

- deltaV (cell volume) was being calculated with the expansion time at
the current timestep (nts) instead of nts_prev. This has been reverted
to use ntsprev, which matches ARTIS classic. The smaller deltaV will
slightly increase normalised values of estimators such as J, nuJ, etc.

- For calculating grey depth of a cell (to decide if it should be
treated in thick/grey mode), the distance to observer is now clamped to
zero. The observer is assumed to be at radial distance xmax, which leads
to negative distances in the cube corners in 3D mode. Setting cells with
grey depth >= 0 would have previously excluded cells in the cube corners
(with negative optical depths).

- if USE_RELATIVISTIC_DOPPLER_SHIFT is on, gamma-ray heating
rpkt_emiss[mgi] is now calculated with relativistic correction, which
fixes an issue with negative gamma heating rates for high velocity cells
(>~0.5c).

### New features

- an artis.pid file keeps track of the (rank 0) process id and prevents
two copies of artis (or artis and exspec) from running simultaneously in
the same directory.
- 3D model.txt files can be read in either one line (previous) or two
line per cell format. The one line per cell format makes file reading
and parsing by standard tools easier. artistools decompresses and reads
these files twice to get even and odd rows, which is slow if xzip is
used on a large model file.
- New option USE_GSL_RANDOM can be set to false to use std::random in
place of GSL's random number generation. So far, this appears to be a
slower method, so it has been switched off.
- Both phixsdata.txt and phixsdata_v2.txt will be read if they both
exist. (Was also added to v2022.11.1)
- New option CLASSIC_LINELIST_SORT can be set to false (default for
kilonova options). The classic line sort function clamps close lines
together and does some memory unsafe things that can result in a
linelist that is not strictly sorted by frequency.
- a new classic 3D test runs a 10^3 model with classic options.
- the classic test now uses a classic atomic dataset (phixsdata.txt)

### Performance improvements
- 1D Sim+2010 subMch model in classic mode with 2e7 packets on 960 cores
(JUWELS) completed 16% faster than v2022.11. Better agreement with
classic, mostly due to the deltaV at nts_prev reversion.
- Reduced lookups of nucindex in decay routines speed up initial
temperature estimation and estimator writing.
- Duplication of atomic transitions in element/ion/level order increases
performance when calculating cooling rates and the macroatom.
- Kilonova models run about 100% faster.
- Use of cumulative sums for macroatom transition probability lists, and
then binary searches speed up do_macroatom, which dominates the runtime
for kilonova models.

### Removals
- The unused packet property scat_count was removed.
- Behaviour according to do_comp_est = false, do_r_lc = true, do_rlc_est
= 3 is always on, and these variables have now been removed.
- SF_USE_LOG_E_INCREMENT. The experimental log energy increment made the
Spencer-Fano solution less accurate and was never used in production
runs.
- DETAILED_BF_ESTIMATORS_BYTYPE. This experimental code was extremely
fragile and memory consuming and did not work in MPI mode.
- NT_BLOCKSIZEEXCITATION. std::vector now handles the dynamic allocation
of the excitation list.
- MINDENSITY. This option didn't actually do anything.
### Renames
- artisoptions: Replace NO_INITIAL_PACKETS with INITIAL_PACKETS_ON
- artisoptions: Replace NO_LUT_PHOTOION with USE_LUT_PHOTOION
- artisoptions: Replace NO_LUT_BFHEATING with USE_LUT_BFHEATING

v2023.5.1 (#36)

Use strict line sort method for all cases to avoid undefined behaviour
(minimal spectral change for classic test) and fix openmp compilation.
Fix for assertion failure cooling_contrib_ion != C_ion when resumed in an LTE timestep with NLTE_POPS_ON

v2023.10 (#40)

New features

- New 2D Cylindrical propagation grid option (for direct mapping of 2D
input models)
- Added test models for various combinations of 1D/2D input models and
1D/2D/3D propagation grids.
- EXPERIMENTAL: Allow hybrid NLTE mode with some elements in full
Non-LTE and other elements in either LTE or photoionisation equilibrium
(classic quasi NLTE). Set with artisoptions.h LEVEL_IS_NLTE()
- EXPERIMENTAL: Enforce Saha ionisation balance (allowing NLTE level
pops) with artisoptions.h FORCE_SAHA_ION_BALANCE() function.
- EXPERIMENTAL: FORCE_SPHERICAL_ESCAPE_SURFACE to remove the corners of
a 2D or 3D model to create a spherical escape surface (allowing for
increased velocity per axis cutoff). Cells with v_r_mid > vmax are set
to empty, and packets found in cells with vel_r_inner > vmax are set to
escaped.

Fixes

- Fix virtual packets (storage of bound-free departure coeff in cell
history had introduced a dependence on the not-updated cell history)
- Fix for bug in 1D spherical grid mode that caused a some packets to
get out of their correct cells. Now ready for production use. Mapping of
1D and 2D models to a 3D Cartesian grid is still possible, but no longer
recommended for new models.
- Fix adiabatic cooling rate with NLTE populations on, replacing nnetot
(free and bound electron density) with nntot (ion plus free electron
density). No change to W7 nebular spectrum.
Fix handling of cell.thick == 2 (optically to vpkt but not rpkt)

Revert change to NLTE matrix normalisation factors (#41)

Use previous ion balance instead of Saha)

Node-share corrphotoion array and shrink estimators to non-empty cells and included ions (#43)

Linting: use trailing return types and avoid redundant void
OpenMP: use nonmonotonic schedule for packet updates

Set vpkts negative line optical depths to zero (#48)

-Set vpkts line optical depths to zero if they are negative. Line
optical depths were never negative in ARTIS-CLASSIC as the level
populations are coming from Boltzmann statistics but population
inversions can occur when running in ARTIS-NLTE resulting in negative
line optical depths. There was previously no check for this for vpkts.
-Set line optical depths to zero in unused function get_tau_sobolev for
consistency
-Add slurm submit script for cosma8 HPC
